{{ infobox bibliographic database | title = Tropicos | image = TropicosLogo.gif | caption = | producer = [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] | country = United States | history = | languages = English, French, Spanish | providers = | cost = [[Open access]] | disciplines = [[Plant taxonomy]] | depth = | formats = | temporal = 1703-present | geospatial = [[Neotropical ecozone]] | number = 4.2 million | updates = | p_title = | p_dates = | ISSN = | web = http://www.tropicos.org/ | titles = }}
'''Tropicos''' is an online [[Botany|botanical]] [[database]] containing taxonomic information on plants, mainly from the [[Neotropical ecozone]] ([[Central America|Central]], and [[South America]]). It is maintained by the [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] and was established over 25 years ago. The database contains images and [[Taxonomy (biology)|taxonomical]] and [[Bibliography|bibliographical]] data on more than 4.2 million [[herbarium]] specimens. In addition, it contains data on over 49,000 scientific publications. The database can be queried in English, French, and Spanish. The oldest records in the database go back to 1703.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://repositorio.fciencias.unam.mx:8080/xmlui/handle/11154/139685?show=full |title=Tropicos |work=Colecciones Bibliográficas para investigación biológica relacionadas y afines |publisher=Ciencias, [[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]] |date=2012-11-05 |accessdate=2014-04-03}}</ref>
